From: Kreijstal <kreijstal@hotmail.com>
Subject: [PATCH] Build cleanly under MinGW-w64

The CMake `if(WIN32)` block force-disables shared libraries; constrain it
to MSVC so MinGW-w64 (and its protobuf-shared deps) can build the DLLs.

`setup.py`'s `os.name == 'nt'` branch hard-codes MSVC import-library
paths. Skip it when Python was built with GCC (mingw-w64) so the unix
build_ext path runs and links against the staged `../build/root` install
through pkg-config.
---
 CMakeLists.txt  | 2 +-
 python/setup.py | 2 +-
 2 files changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/CMakeLists.txt b/CMakeLists.txt
--- a/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -46,7 +46,7 @@ if (SPM_CROSS_SYSTEM_PROCESSOR)
 endif()

 # Disable shared build on windows
-if(WIN32)
+if(MSVC)
   set(SPM_ENABLE_SHARED OFF)
 endif()

diff --git a/python/setup.py b/python/setup.py
--- a/python/setup.py
+++ b/python/setup.py
@@ -161,7 +161,7 @@ def get_win_arch():
   return arch


-if os.name == 'nt':
+if os.name == 'nt' and 'GCC' not in sys.version:
   # Must pre-install sentencepice into build directory.
   arch = get_win_arch()
   if os.path.exists('..\\build\\root_{}\\lib'.format(arch)):
